Elbit, Teva, Allium, Lifewave, Ocif: Israeli Equity Preview

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-04-10T06:41:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-10/elbit-teva-allium-lifewave-ocif-israeli-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Israeli markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
the company names and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index lost 1.3 percent to 1,317.69 in  Tel Aviv .  Allium Medical Solutions Ltd. (ALMD)  : The medical
technology company’s prostate stent won a medical design award.
Allium jumped 11 percent to 0.629 shekel.  Elbit Systems Ltd. (ESLT)  :  Israel ’s biggest non-
government defense contractor filed a $100 million lawsuit in
the  High Court  of Justice of the U.K. against the Government of
 Georgia  for failure to pay amounts due to the company under
contracts signed in 2007. Elbit fell 1.6 percent to 187 shekels.  Isras Investment Company Ltd. (ISRS IT): The building
company’s board approved the acquisition of OCIF Investments and
Development Ltd.(OCIF IT) Separately, Moody’s Midroog lowered
its outlook on Isras to “negative” from “positive.” Isras
rose 0.8 percent to 130 shekels the last time it traded on April
4. Ocif climbed 4.6 percent to 17.72 shekels.  Lifewave Ltd. (LIFE)  : The maker of medical equipment
said it raised 2.2 million shekels ($640,465) from a share sale.
Lifewave plunged 18 percent to 1.982 shekels.  Teva Pharmaceuticals Industries Ltd. (TEVA IT): Merck &
Co., the second-biggest U.S. drug company, lost a U.K. appeal to
reinstate its European patent for the glaucoma treatment Cosopt
after a successful challenge by the world’s largest maker of
generic drugs. Teva gained 0.4 percent to 176.20 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in Tel Aviv at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
